#: src/AbilitiesService.php:38
msgid "Ask me to find saved recipes by title, ingredient, category, or tag."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:39
msgid "Ask me to import a recipe from a URL, create a recipe variation, or help plan meals for the week."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:65
msgid "When presenting Cookbook recipes, include the recipe title and link it with view_url when present."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:69
msgid "When presenting Cookbook search results, show concise recipe matches and link each recipe with view_url when present. If no recipes match, say that no Cookbook recipe was found instead of guessing from the database."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:73
msgid "When presenting Cookbook week plans, summarize planned meals by day and meal slot. Link planned recipes with their view_url when present, and link to the planner using the returned url."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:91
msgid "Abilities for working with Cookbook recipes and week plans."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:107
msgid "Search Cookbook Recipes"
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:108
msgid "Searches Cookbook recipes and returns matching recipe summaries."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:116
msgid "Use this when the user asks to find, list, filter, or choose Cookbook recipes. Call without input to list the latest 10 recipes. Return recipe IDs for follow-up get-recipe calls, and use view_url when linking results to the user."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:129
msgid "Get Cookbook Recipe"
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:130
msgid "Returns one structured Cookbook recipe by ID."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:138
msgid "Recipe post ID."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:148
msgid "Use this when the user asks about one known Cookbook recipe. The response includes view_url for linking, flat compatibility ingredients/instructions, named parts for ingredient or instruction sections, notes, taxonomy terms, and variation family data."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:161
msgid "Save Cookbook Recipe"
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:162
msgid "Creates a structured Cookbook recipe, or updates an existing recipe when an ID is provided."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:170
msgid "Use this when the user asks to save, create, or update a structured Cookbook recipe. Pass parts to preserve named ingredient or instruction sections; flat ingredients and instructions remain supported for unsectioned recipes. To add or replace a recipe photo, pass the existing recipe id with image_url. Prefer create-recipe-variation when adapting an existing recipe into a new variation. Link the result using view_url."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:183
msgid "Import Cookbook Recipe"
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:184
msgid "Imports a recipe from source_url or pasted recipe text and publishes it."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:191
msgid "Recipe page URL to parse."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:195
msgid "Plain recipe text to parse if no URL can be parsed."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:199
#: src/AbilitiesService.php:652
msgid "Optional image URL to sideload as the recipe photo."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:209
msgid "Use this when the user provides a recipe URL, pasted recipe text, or an image URL to import into Cookbook. This publishes the recipe; link the result using view_url."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:222
msgid "Create Cookbook Recipe Variation"
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:223
msgid "Creates a child recipe variation from an existing Cookbook recipe, copying omitted fields from the source."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:231
msgid "Use this when the user asks for an adapted version of an existing recipe, such as substituting an ingredient they do not have. First call get-recipe for the source, then pass the complete revised recipe fields here so omitted fields intentionally copy from the source. If the source has named parts, pass revised parts to preserve ingredient subsection headers. Link the created variation using view_url."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:244
msgid "Get Cookbook Week Plan"
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:245
msgid "Returns the signed-in user's week planner for a normalized week."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:253
msgid "Use this when the user asks what meals are planned for a week. The week_start input can be any date in the week; use the returned url to link to the planner."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:266
msgid "Save Cookbook Week Plan"
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:267
msgid "Saves recipe IDs into the signed-in user's week planner meal slots."
msgstr ""

#: src/AbilitiesService.php:275
msgid "Use this when the user asks to add, move, clear, or replace recipes in their week planner. This can clear slots with recipe ID 0 or replace the whole week when replace is true, so confirm ambiguous planner edits before executing."
msgstr ""

